text: Nummi-Pusula is a former municipality in Finland. It was formed in 1981 from the existing municipalities of Nummi and Pusula. The municipality is in Uusimaa and in the province of Southern Finland. On 1 January 2013, it became a part of Lohja. Nummi-Pusula has an area of . of it is water. About 6,175 people lived there as of 31 December 2012. == Other websites == * The official Nummi-Pusula page , in Finnish, English, German and Estonian Category:Former municipalities of Finland Category:1981 establishments in Europe Category:1980s establishments in Finland
